<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="8.[264,1322,1217,1804]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,439,1217,1243]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Zhang &amp; Zhu &amp; Song, 2005" authorityName="Zhang &amp; Zhu &amp; Song" authorityYear="2005" box="[742,984,1218,1243]" class="Arachnida" family="Oxyopidae" genus="Hamataliwa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cordata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[742,984,1218,1243]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Hamataliwa cordata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[992,1082,1218,1244]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
in female epigynum with a heart­like depression, but it differs from the latter in copulatory ducts of female epigynum long and swollen at the base (
<figureCitation box="[726,817,1298,1324]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–15" captionStartId="9.[264,382,1372,1396]" captionTargetBox="[276,1319,312,1343]" captionTargetId="figure-129@9.[264,1323,300,1344]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 11–15. Hamataliwa labialis (Song, 1991), 11–13, female holotype. 11, body, dorsal view; 12, epigyne, ventral view; 13, vulva, dorsal view; 14–15, male paratype. 14, male left palp, ventral view; 15, male left palp, retrolateral view. Scale bars: 11, 1.0mm; 12–15, 0.2mm." pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
); tip of median apophysis of male palpal organ beak­shaped, conductor relatively simple, with a lateral lobe and a triangular process, ventral tibial apophysis small and club­like, retrolateral tibial apophysis flat (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 11–15" captionStartId="9.[264,382,1372,1396]" captionTargetBox="[276,1319,312,1343]" captionTargetId="figure-129@9.[264,1323,300,1344]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 11–15. Hamataliwa labialis (Song, 1991), 11–13, female holotype. 11, body, dorsal view; 12, epigyne, ventral view; 13, vulva, dorsal view; 14–15, male paratype. 14, male left palp, ventral view; 15, male left palp, retrolateral view. Scale bars: 11, 1.0mm; 12–15, 0.2mm." pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Figs. 14–15</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="11" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="8.[264,1322,1217,1804]" box="[312,493,1457,1483]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,493,1457,1483]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Redescription.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[264,1322,1217,1804]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
Female (
<typeStatus box="[413,523,1498,1524]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">holotype</typeStatus>
): Total length 5.16. Prosoma 2.58 long, 2.10 wide; opisthosoma 2.39 long, 1.67 wide. Carapace red brown, with some white hairs and brown streaks; eyes area black brown. Chelicerae with two promarginal and one retromarginal teeth. Labium longer than wide, with dark patches on basal half.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[264,1322,1217,1804]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Opisthosoma oval; dorsum white yellow, with two pairs of brown spots and five chevron­shaped brown bands across horizontal axis, posterior half of dorsum grayish laterally; venter with a mesal wide brownish longitudinal stripe behind the epigastric furrow.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[264,1322,1217,1804]" box="[312,1290,1778,1804]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Legs orange, with dark brown annulations from femora to tarsi. Leg formula: 1234.</paragraph>
<caption pageId="9" pageNumber="10" startId="9.[264,382,1372,1396]" targetBox="[276,1319,312,1343]" targetPageId="9">
<paragraph blockId="9.[264,1322,1372,1473]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[264,464,1372,1396]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">FIGURES 11–15.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="(Song, 1991)" authorityName="Zhang &amp; Zhu &amp; Song" authorityYear="2005" baseAuthorityName="Song" baseAuthorityYear="1991" box="[475,854,1373,1396]" class="Arachnida" family="Oxyopidae" genus="Hamataliwa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="labialis">
<emphasis box="[475,698,1373,1396]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Hamataliwa labialis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Song, D. X." box="[716,845,1373,1396]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="169 - 181" refId="ref6780" refString="Song, D. X. (1991) On lynx spiders of the genus Oxyopes (Araneae: Oxyopidae) from China. Sinozoologia, 8, 169 - 181." type="journal article" year="1991">Song, 1991</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 11–13, female holotype. 11, body, dorsal view; 12, epigyne, ventral view; 13, vulva, dorsal view; 14–15, male paratype. 14, male left palp, ventral view; 15, male left palp, retrolateral view. Scale bars: 11, 1.0mm; 12–15, 0.2mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="9.[312,541,1529,1555]" box="[312,541,1529,1555]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Leg measurements:</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[277,1201,1604,1747]" box="[393,1201,1604,1627]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">femur patella+tibia metatarsus tarsus total</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[277,1201,1604,1747]" box="[277,1200,1636,1659]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">I 2.55 3.06 1.90 0.94 8.45</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[277,1201,1604,1747]" box="[277,1200,1665,1688]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">II 2.36 2.75 1.74 0.82 7.67</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[277,1201,1604,1747]" box="[277,1200,1695,1718]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">III 1.94 2.10 1.48 0.72 6.24</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[277,1201,1604,1747]" box="[277,1200,1724,1747]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">IV 1.71 1.97 1.52 0.68 5.88</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[264,1322,1799,1905]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
Epigynum as illustrated (
<figureCitation box="[604,744,1799,1825]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–15" captionStartId="9.[264,382,1372,1396]" captionTargetBox="[276,1319,312,1343]" captionTargetId="figure-129@9.[264,1323,300,1344]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 11–15. Hamataliwa labialis (Song, 1991), 11–13, female holotype. 11, body, dorsal view; 12, epigyne, ventral view; 13, vulva, dorsal view; 14–15, male paratype. 14, male left palp, ventral view; 15, male left palp, retrolateral view. Scale bars: 11, 1.0mm; 12–15, 0.2mm." pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Figs. 12–13</figureCitation>
); posterior depression small and somewhat heartlike, with intromittent orifices at the anterior end of its lateral edges; base of copulatory ducts swollen, spermathecae round.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[264,1323,284,430]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Male. Total length 4.45. Prosoma 2.13 long, 1.74 wide; opisthosoma 1.94 long, 1.50 wide. Dorsum of opisthosoma with some brownish spots. Leg IV darker than leg III. Other characters similar to those of female. Leg formula: 1234.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[264,1323,284,430]" box="[312,547,404,430]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Palp measurements:</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[277,1200,482,542]" box="[393,1200,482,505]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">femur patella Tibia tarsus total</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[277,1200,482,542]" box="[277,1200,519,542]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">palp 0.89 0.32 0.35 0.94 2.50</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[312,541,596,622]" box="[312,541,596,622]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Leg measurements:</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[277,1201,674,839]" box="[393,1201,674,697]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">femur patella+tibia metatarsus tarsus total</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[277,1201,674,839]" box="[277,1200,711,734]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">I 2.39 2.90 1.90 0.91 8.10</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[277,1201,674,839]" box="[277,1200,746,769]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">II 2.26 2.81 1.77 0.81 7.65</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[277,1201,674,839]" box="[277,1200,781,804]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">III 1.77 2.20 1.45 0.72 6.14</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[277,1201,674,839]" box="[277,1200,816,839]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">IV 1.55 1.90 1.42 0.70 5.57</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[264,1323,893,1159]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Male palp as illustrated (
<figureCitation box="[606,748,893,919]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–15" captionStartId="9.[264,382,1372,1396]" captionTargetBox="[276,1319,312,1343]" captionTargetId="figure-129@9.[264,1323,300,1344]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 11–15. Hamataliwa labialis (Song, 1991), 11–13, female holotype. 11, body, dorsal view; 12, epigyne, ventral view; 13, vulva, dorsal view; 14–15, male paratype. 14, male left palp, ventral view; 15, male left palp, retrolateral view. Scale bars: 11, 1.0mm; 12–15, 0.2mm." pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Figs. 14–15</figureCitation>
); basal outgrowth of cymbium almost triangular in ventral view; median apophysis longitudinal and slightly sclerotized, with its tip beakshaped; embolus long, with small basal twist, the membranous process indistinct, its distal part flagelliform and accompanying conductor; conductor with lateral lobe and distal triangular process; in lateral view, ventral tibial apophysis thumb­like, and retrolateral tibial apophysis flat..
</paragraph>
